@startuml OnlineShoppingSystem_Original_Annotated

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam ranksep 30
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
    HeaderBackgroundColor #27AE60
}

skinparam enum {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam interface {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

title <size:18>Online Shopping System - Class Diagram (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Customer registers, searches product, adds to cart, places order, pays, tracks delivery."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE — OnlineShoppingSystem
' ====================================================================
class OnlineShoppingSystem {
    - customers : Map<String, Customer>
    - orders : Map<String, Order>
    - products : Map<String, Product>
    - paymentService : PaymentService
    - orderService : OrderService
    - searchService : SearchService
    --
    + {static} getInstance() : OnlineShoppingSystem
    + registerCustomer(name, email, addr) : Customer
    + placeOrder(customerId, String, PaymentStrategy) : Order
    + searchProducts(query) : List
    + getShoppingCart(customerId) : ShoppingCart
}

note top of OnlineShoppingSystem #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "Client only talks to this class.
    It's the **Facade** — hides OrderService,
    PaymentService, SearchService behind
    one clean API. Customer registers,
    then searches for a product."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: CUSTOMER + ACCOUNT + ADDRESS
' ====================================================================
class Customer {
    - id : String
    - name : String
    - email : String
    - account : Account
    - shippingAddress : Address
    - orders : List<Order>
    --
    + updateProfile() : void
    + getOrderHistory() : List<Order>
}

class Account {
    - username : String
    - password : String
    - cart : ShoppingCart
}

class Address {
    - street : String
    - city : String
    - state : String
    - zipCode : String
    - country : String
}

note left of Customer #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - Customer model.**
    "Customer has Account (auth)
    and Address (shipping).
    Account holds ShoppingCart.
    Each class = one job." **(SRP)**
end note

Customer *-- Account : has >
Customer *-- Address : lives at >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: PRODUCT + DECORATOR
' ====================================================================
interface Product <<Interface>> {
    + getId() : String
    + getName() : String
    + getPrice() : double
    + getCategory() : ProductCategory
    + getDescription() : String
}

class BaseProduct {
    - id : String
    - name : String
    - price : double
    - description : String
    - category : ProductCategory
}

enum ProductCategory {
    CLOTHING
    ELECTRONICS
    GROCERY
    BOOKS
}

abstract class ProductDecorator {
    # wrappedProduct : Product
    --
    + getName() : String
    + getPrice() : double
}

class GiftWrapDecorator {
    - wrapCost : double
    - wrapDescription : String
    --
    + getPrice() : double
    + getDescription() : String
}

note bottom of ProductDecorator #FFE0B2
    **STEP 3 - Customer picks a product.**
    "Wants gift wrap? Instead of subclass
    explosion (GiftWrappedElectronics...),
    **Decorator** adds cost at runtime:
    new GiftWrapDecorator(baseProduct).
    Composable, extensible."
    **Pattern: Decorator | OCP**
end note

Product <|.. BaseProduct
Product <|.. ProductDecorator
ProductDecorator o--> Product : wraps >
ProductDecorator <|-- GiftWrapDecorator
BaseProduct --> ProductCategory : categorized by >


' ====================================================================
'  SEARCH SERVICE
' ====================================================================
class SearchService {
    - productCatalog : Collection<Product>
    --
    + searchByName(query) : List<Product>
    + searchByCategory(cat) : List<Product>
    + filterByPriceRange(min, max) : List<Product>
}

SearchService --> Product : searches >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: SHOPPING CART
' ====================================================================
class ShoppingCart {
    - items : Map<String, CartItem>
    --
    + addItem(product, qty) : void
    + removeItem(productId) : void
    + getItems() : Map<String, CartItem>
    + clearCart() : void
    + getTotal() : double
}

class CartItem {
    - quantity : int
    - product : Product
    --
    + getSubtotal() : double
}

note left of ShoppingCart #E1BEE7
    **STEP 4 - Adds to cart.**
    "Customer adds (decorated) product.
    Cart holds CartItems. On checkout,
    cart items become OrderLineItems."
end note

ShoppingCart *-- CartItem : contains >
CartItem --> Product : references >
Account --> ShoppingCart : owns >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: ORDER + SERVICES
' ====================================================================
class Order {
    - id : String
    - customer : Customer
    - status : OrderStatus
    - currentState : OrderState
    - shippingAddress : Address
    - items : List<OrderLineItem>
    - orderDate : LocalDateTime
    - observers : List<OrderObserver>
    --
    + shipOrder() : void
    + deliverOrder() : void
    + cancelOrder() : void
    + registerObserver(o) : void
    + notifyObservers() : void
}

class OrderLineItem {
    - quantity : int
    - price : double
    - product : Product
    --
    + getLineTotal() : double
}

enum OrderStatus {
    PLACED
    SHIPPED
    PENDING_PAYMENT
    DELIVERED
    CANCELLED
    RETURNED
}

note top of Order #FFCDD2
    **STEP 5 - Order created.**
    "OrderService validates stock, creates
    Order. This is the **central object**.
    It uses **State** (lifecycle) and
    **Observer** (notifications)."
end note

Order *-- OrderLineItem : contains >
Order --> OrderStatus : tracks >
OrderLineItem --> Product : for >
Customer --> Order : places >

class OrderService {
    - inventoryService : InventoryService
    --
    + createOrder(customer, items) : Order
    + validateOrder(order) : boolean
}

class InventoryService {
    - stock : Map<String, Integer>
    --
    + checkStock(productId) : boolean
    + updateStock(productId, qty) : void
    + addStock(productId, qty) : void
}

OrderService --> InventoryService : checks stock >
OrderService --> Order : creates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: STATE PATTERN
' ====================================================================
interface OrderState <<State>> {
    + handleOrder(order) : void
    + shipOrder(order) : void
    + deliverOrder(order) : void
    + cancelOrder(order) : void
}

class PlacedState {
    + handleOrder(order) : void
    + shipOrder(order) : void
    + cancelOrder(order) : void
}

class ShippedState {
    + deliverOrder(order) : void
    + cancelOrder(order) : void
}

class DeliveredState {
    + handleOrder(order) : void
}

class CancelledState {
    + handleOrder(order) : void
}

note bottom of OrderState #FFCDD2
    **STEP 6 - State transitions.**
    "**State Pattern** — each state is a class.
    No if-else chains in Order.
    PlacedState: can ship or cancel.
    ShippedState: can deliver or cancel.
    Delivered/Cancelled = terminal."
    Placed -> Shipped -> Delivered
    Placed/Shipped -> Cancelled
    **Pattern: State | SRP, OCP**
end note

OrderState <|.. PlacedState
OrderState <|.. ShippedState
OrderState <|.. DeliveredState
OrderState <|.. CancelledState
Order --> OrderState : delegates lifecycle >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: OBSERVER PATTERN
' ====================================================================
interface Subject <<Observable>> {
    + registerObserver(o) : void
    + removeObserver(o) : void
    + notifyObservers() : void
}

interface OrderObserver <<Observer>> {
    + update(order) : void
}

class EmailNotificationObserver {
    - emailAddress : String
    --
    + update(order) : void
}

class PushNotificationObserver {
    - deviceToken : String
    --
    + update(order) : void
}

note left of Subject #B2EBF2
    **STEP 7 - Notifications.**
    "On every state change, Order
    calls notifyObservers().
    **Observer Pattern** — Order doesn't
    know how to send email/push.
    Add SMS? One new observer.
    Order unchanged."
    **Pattern: Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

Order ..|> Subject
Subject --> OrderObserver : notifies >
OrderObserver <|.. EmailNotificationObserver
OrderObserver <|.. PushNotificationObserver


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: PAYMENT — Strategy
' ====================================================================
class PaymentService {
    --
    + processPayment(strategy, amount) : boolean
}

interface PaymentStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + pay(amount) : boolean
}

class CreditCardPaymentStrategy {
    - cardNumber : String
    - expiryDate : String
    --
    + pay(amount) : boolean
}

class UpiPaymentStrategy {
    - upiId : String
    --
    + pay(amount) : boolean
}

note right of PaymentStrategy #D1C4E9
    **STEP 8 - Customer pays.**
    "How they pay varies. **Strategy
    Pattern** — PaymentService delegates
    to PaymentStrategy interface.
    CreditCard, UPI are swappable.
    Add PayPal? One new class."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP, LSP**
end note

PaymentService --> PaymentStrategy : delegates >
PaymentStrategy <|.. CreditCardPaymentStrategy
PaymentStrategy <|.. UpiPaymentStrategy


' ====================================================================
'  FACADE RELATIONSHIPS
' ====================================================================
OnlineShoppingSystem --> Customer : manages >
OnlineShoppingSystem --> OrderService : uses >
OnlineShoppingSystem --> PaymentService : uses >
OnlineShoppingSystem --> SearchService : uses >


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "We traced a full journey: register -> search
    -> decorate (gift wrap) -> cart -> order -> state transitions
    -> notifications -> payment. **5 patterns**: Facade, Decorator,
    State, Observer, Strategy. Each solves a real problem."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | Customer visits, registers via Facade | Facade | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | Customer / Account / Address models | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | Searches product, adds gift wrap | Decorator | OCP |
    | 4 | Adds to ShoppingCart | -- | SRP |
    | 5 | Places order, stock validated, Order created | -- | SRP |
    | 6 | Order: Placed -> Shipped -> Delivered / Cancelled | State | SRP, OCP |
    | 7 | On state change, email/push observers notified | Observer | OCP, SRP |
    | 8 | Payment via CreditCard / UPI strategy | Strategy | OCP, DIP, LSP |
endlegend

@enduml
